WITH customer_primary_channels AS (
  SELECT 
    customer_id,
    channel,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY customer_id ORDER BY attributed_at DESC) as attribution_rank
  FROM customer_channels
)
SELECT 
  c.customer_id,
  COALESCE(pc.channel, 'No Channel') as primary_channel
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN customer_primary_channels pc ON c.customer_id = pc.customer_id AND pc.attribution_rank = 1;

-- revenue_by_channel_city.sql
```sql
WITH customer_primary_channels AS (
  SELECT 
    customer_id,
    channel,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY customer_id ORDER BY attributed_at DESC) as attribution_rank
  FROM customer_channels
),
customer_channels_map AS (
  SELECT 
    c.customer_id,
    COALESCE(pc.channel, 'No Channel') as primary_channel
  FROM customers c
  LEFT JOIN customer_primary_channels pc ON c.customer_id = pc.customer_id AND pc.attribution_rank = 1
)
SELECT 
  ccm.primary_channel as channel,
  COALESCE(s.city, 'Unknown Store') as city,
  SUM(t.amount) as total_revenue,
  COUNT(t.transaction_id) as transaction_count,
  COUNT(DISTINCT t.customer_id) as unique_customers
FROM transactions t
INNER JOIN customer_channels_map ccm ON t.customer_id = ccm.customer_id
LEFT JOIN stores s ON t.store_id = s.store_id
GROUP BY ccm.primary_channel, s.city
ORDER BY ccm.primary_channel, s.city;
